# bluetooth keyboard auto loader
Scripts to auto pair a bluetooth keyboard to current device and hook it to the usb output on a pi zero (built for a Keychron K2)
For other types of solutions https://github.com/Gadgetoid/pi400kb is probably the best aproach 
Use evtest for debugging

## Requirements
* bluetoothctl

## Systemd
Copy bluetooth-keyboard-.service to /etc/systemd/system
create symlink at /etc/systemd/system/multi-user.target.wants/
run `sudo source scripts/bootstrap_keyboard_config.sh`
